12_6	0.0	The Fitzpatrick sisters are two of the 2,240 Palm Beach County students who may sit barefoot at their kitchen desks this year, while their parents put on teaching caps.
12_7	0.0	Since 1994, their numbers have tripled in Palm Beach County and nearly doubled statewide.
12_8	3.0	There were 31,440 Florida students home schooled last year.
12_9	0.2727272727272727	In Palm Beach County, home-schooled students must register with the district superintendent's office.
12_10	0.0	State law also requires them to keep a portfolio that can be shown to the superintendent on 15 days' notice.
12_11	0.0	The rapidly increasing numbers may be due, in part, to new state laws.
12_12	0.2727272727272727	In 1996, home-schooled students were allowed to participate in sports and music programs at high schools.
12_13	0.0	And as of May 1997, they may apply to two-year colleges with merely an affidavit signed by their parent.
